## Phase 2: `genotypes='counts'`

### Output Type

`genotypes STRUCT(hom_ref UINTEGER, het UINTEGER, hom_alt UINTEGER, missing UINTEGER)`

One struct per row, counting genotype classes across the opposite dimension:
- **Variant orient**: counts across samples for each variant
- **Sample orient**: counts across variants for each sample

### Performance

In variant orient, uses `PgrGetCounts()` — no genotype decompression needed.
This is the same fast path as `plink_freq`. For 100K+ sample cohorts this is
orders of magnitude faster than reading all genotypes.

In sample orient, counts are accumulated from the pre-read genotype matrix
(already materialized at bind time).

### Orient Compatibility

| Orient | counts | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| variant | ✓ | PgrGetCounts per variant — fast |
| sample | ✓ | Accumulate from pre-read matrix |
| genotype | ✗ error | Counts are aggregates, not per-genotype |

### Parameter Compatibility

| Parameter | Compatible | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| `phased := true` | ✗ error | Counts have no phase information |
| `dosages := true` | ✗ error | Counts are discrete |
| `genotype_range` | ✓ | Counts reflect post-range-filtered genotypes |
| `af_range`/`ac_range` | ✓ | Variant-level filter, orthogonal |
| `samples` | ✓ | PgrGetCounts supports sample subsetting |

### Scan Implementation (variant orient)

```cpp
// Claim batch of variants (existing pattern)
// For each variant:
STD_ARRAY_DECL(uint32_t, 4, genocounts);
PgrGetCounts(sample_include, interleaved_vec, pssi, sample_ct, vidx, &pgr, genocounts);

// Fill STRUCT children
auto &entries = StructVector::GetEntries(genotypes_vec);
FlatVector::GetData<uint32_t>(*entries[0])[row] = genocounts[0]; // hom_ref
FlatVector::GetData<uint32_t>(*entries[1])[row] = genocounts[1]; // het
FlatVector::GetData<uint32_t>(*entries[2])[row] = genocounts[2]; // hom_alt
FlatVector::GetData<uint32_t>(*entries[3])[row] = genocounts[3]; // missing
```

### Scan Implementation (sample orient)

```cpp
// Accumulate from pre-read matrix
uint32_t counts[4] = {0, 0, 0, 0};
for (idx_t v = 0; v < effective_variant_ct; v++) {
    int8_t geno = genotype_matrix[v][sample_pos];
    if (geno == -9) counts[3]++;
    else counts[geno]++;
}
```

